B I G NEWS!!!✨🤩 I am beyond excited to announce that my school is opening a Prep Kangaroos class (an additional Mon & Tues class) from the beginning of Term 3!

You have allllll been asking for the longest time to see what Prep is *really* like. I am so unbelievably excited to show you how incredible it is! As the Dean of Junior Primary and teaching the Monday-Wednesday (Koalas) Prep class I may be slightly biased. I created this video for the lovely place in which I work to allow you to have a proper glimpse into our exciting Prep programme that aims to begin our students’ schooling journey exactly as it should: encouraging children to WANT to learn.

{For those in our area, apply NOW to reserve a place for your child at the Macarthur region's leading Christian Independent Preparatory School. Application link via bio at @st_petersanglican @invite_to_learn or at https://www.stpeters.nsw.edu.au/admissions/how-to-apply/ (Note: children on the existing waiting list receive first preference.)}

MATHEMATICAL LANGUAGE + capacity + fun!!🌈🎉 “Which one says it’s full? Mine is full now! It was nearly full, but now it’s full because there is no more space left in the jar.” It’s alllll in the play and conversations! 

This can be done just as easily in a small tray. You can use water, chickpeas, sand or even dirt. Try to use a variety of containers. I usually add spoons too. To use this kind of activity as an assessment opportunity with Kindergarten or Pre-Kindergarten I’d ask them to take a photo of the label with their container when it matches the word/s. You could then use those photos on the wall as documentation of learning. Alternatively you could have students draw in individual or whole class learning journals. {Note: the black tray is a tuff tray. The labels are from @twinklaustralia ✨}

At home, I’d opt for water or sand outdoors, or chickpeas indoors (as these are easier to tidy quickly). Work is easier to clean up as we have a stick vacuum. Hubby is convinced we need a new one at home but 💸💸 when our 20 yr old @dyson still works?? I don’t know. Do you have a stick vac? What brand? Is it worth the money?? Jen @living_future_memories 
